---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ModuleCompleteButton from '../../components/ModuleCompleteButton.astro';
import CardOfTheDay from '../../components/CardOfTheDay.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Module 6: Fearless Reading — The Fearless Tarot" description="Break free from memorization. Learn to read intuitively, work with reversals, and develop your unique reading voice.">
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <p class="font-accent text-hotpink text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">✦ Module 6 ✦</p>
      <div class="text-6xl mb-4">⚡</div>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-5xl sm:text-6xl text-moonlight mb-3"
          style="text-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(255,105,180,0.5);">
        The Fearless Reader
      </h1>
      <p class="font-accent text-hotpink text-lg">Intuitive Reading Mastery</p>
      <div class="mt-4 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-hotpink/40 to-transparent"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <p class="text-silver text-lg leading-relaxed text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">
      The most powerful reading you'll ever give comes <strong class="text-hotpink">not from memory, but from presence</strong>.
      This module is about releasing the training wheels — the guidebook, the memorized keywords, the fear of getting it "wrong" —
      and stepping into the fearless, intuitive reader you were born to be.
    </p>

    <!-- Objectives -->
    <section class="mb-10 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-hotpink/30 bg-hotpink/5">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-moonlight mb-4">✦ Learning Objectives</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2">
        {[
          "Read cards intuitively without constantly referencing books or keywords",
          "Interpret card combinations and understand how cards modify each other",
          "Work confidently with reversed cards using multiple approaches",
          "Develop your unique reading voice, style, and philosophy"
        ].map(obj => (
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-silver text-sm">
            <span class="text-hotpink mt-0.5">✦</span>
            {obj}
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Intuitive Reading -->
    <section class="space-y-8 mb-12">
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl text-moonlight mb-4">Reading Intuitively</h2>
        <p class="text-silver/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Intuitive reading means <strong class="text-teal">trusting your own responses</strong> to a card before reaching for
          any external meaning. Your gut reaction — the feeling in your body, the word that surfaces, the memory that appears —
          is always the first and most important layer of interpretation.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          {[
            { step: "1", title: "Look Before You Think", desc: "Spend 30 seconds just looking at the card. What do you notice? What feeling arises? What single word comes to mind?" },
            { step: "2", title: "Tell the Story", desc: "Without using the card's traditional name or meaning, tell the story of what you SEE happening in the image." },
            { step: "3", title: "Make It Personal", desc: "Ask: 'How does this story relate to my question or situation?' The bridge between imagery and meaning is always personal." },
            { step: "4", title: "Then Consult Tradition", desc: "After your intuitive read, look at traditional meanings. Notice what aligned. Be surprised by what didn't." },
          ].map(item => (
            <div class="flex gap-4 p-4 rounded-xl border border-charcoal/40 bg-charcoal/10">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-hotpink/20 border border-hotpink/40 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                <span class="font-accent text-hotpink text-xs">{item.step}</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="font-accent text-silver text-sm mb-1">{item.title}</p>
                <p class="text-silver/60 text-xs">{item.desc}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Card Combinations -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl text-moonlight mb-4">Reading Card Combinations</h2>
        <p class="text-silver/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          When two or more cards appear together, they create a <strong class="text-teal">conversation</strong>. They can support each other,
          modify each other, or create tension that points to a nuanced truth.
        </p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
          {[
            { type: "Harmonious", desc: "Cards that share an element or theme amplify each other's message.", example: "Three of Cups + The Sun = Pure joy and celebration ahead" },
            { type: "Modifying", desc: "One card changes how you interpret the other.", example: "The Tower + The Star = Disruption followed by hope and renewal" },
            { type: "Tension", desc: "Opposing energies creating a nuanced message or choice point.", example: "The Hermit + Three of Wands = Alone but visionary — solitude serving expansion" },
          ].map(combo => (
            <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-teal/20 bg-teal/5">
              <p class="font-accent text-teal text-xs uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">{combo.type}</p>
              <p class="text-silver/70 text-xs mb-2">{combo.desc}</p>
              <p class="text-silver/50 text-xs italic">{combo.example}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Reversals -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl text-moonlight mb-4">Working with Reversals</h2>
        <p class="text-silver/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Whether you work with reversals is entirely your choice. There is no "correct" approach. Here are the main approaches:
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          {[
            { title: "Blocked Energy", desc: "The card's energy is present but blocked, delayed, or not yet fully expressed." },
            { title: "Internalized", desc: "The energy is turned inward — working on an inner level rather than externally manifesting." },
            { title: "Shadow Aspect", desc: "The darker, more challenging expression of the card's archetype is at play." },
            { title: "The Message is Extra Strong", desc: "Some readers treat reversals as intensified versions of the upright meaning." },
            { title: "Ignore Reversals", desc: "Many excellent readers simply read all cards upright and focus on intuition and context." },
          ].map(approach => (
            <div class="flex gap-3 text-sm">
              <span class="text-violet mt-0.5">✦</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-accent text-silver">{approach.title}: </span>
                <span class="text-silver/70">{approach.desc}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Practice with Card of the Day -->
    <section class="mb-10 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-hotpink/30 bg-hotpink/5">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-hotpink mb-3">🎯 Activity: Eyes-Closed Pull & Story</h2>
      <p class="text-silver/80 text-sm mb-4">
        Use the card randomizer below. When your card appears, set a timer for 3 minutes and write
        <em>without stopping</em> about what you see and feel — no keywords, no "meanings." Just your raw response.
        Then pull another and do the same.
      </p>
      <CardOfTheDay />
    </section>

    <!-- Building Your Style -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl text-moonlight mb-6">Building Your Reading Style</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        {[
          { q: "Do you use reversals?", options: ["Yes, always", "Sometimes", "Never"] },
          { q: "What's your reading philosophy?", options: ["Predictive", "Empowerment", "Psychological", "Spiritual"] },
          { q: "What's your reading environment?", options: ["Sacred ritual", "Casual & conversational", "Meditative", "Practical"] },
          { q: "How do you begin a reading?", options: ["Set intention", "Shuffle & pray", "Ask a question", "Just dive in"] },
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-charcoal/40 bg-charcoal/10">
            <p class="font-accent text-violet text-xs uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">{item.q}</p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              {item.options.map(opt => (
                <span class="font-accent text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full border border-charcoal/60 text-silver/60">{opt}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p class="text-silver/50 text-xs mt-4 text-center font-accent italic">
        There are no right answers — only your answers. Your reading style is uniquely yours.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Discussion -->
    <section class="mb-10 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-hotpink/20 bg-hotpink/5">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-hotpink mb-4">💬 Discussion Prompts</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-silver/80 text-sm">
        {[
          "When do you trust your intuition vs. defer to traditional meanings?",
          "How do you handle reversals in your personal practice?",
          "What makes a reading feel meaningful and authentic to you?"
        ].map(q => (
          <li class="flex gap-2 italic"><span class="text-hotpink not-italic">Q:</span>{q}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Navigation -->
    <div class="flex justify-between items-center mt-12 pt-6 border-t border-charcoal/30">
      <a href="/modules/5-spreads" class="font-accent text-violet hover:text-teal transition-colors text-sm">
        ← Module 5: Spreads
      </a>
      <a href="/modules/7-read-for-others" class="font-accent text-violet hover:text-teal transition-colors text-sm">
        Module 7: Read for Others →
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center">
      <ModuleCompleteButton moduleId={6} />
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
